Token Ring Algorithm

class TokenRing:

    def __init__(self, num_nodes):
        self.num_nodes = num_nodes
        self.nodes = [None] * num_nodes

    def set_node(self, node_id, data):
        self.nodes[node_id] = data

    def run(self):

        current_node = 0

        for i in range(self.num_nodes):

            token = self.nodes[current_node]

            print(f"Node {current_node}: "
                  f"Received token with data '{token}'")

            print(f"Node {current_node}: "
                  f"Processing data "
                  f"'{self.nodes[current_node]}'")

            # Pass token to next node
            current_node = (current_node + 1) % self.num_nodes


# Create ring
token_ring = TokenRing(4)

# Add data
token_ring.set_node(0, "Data 1")
token_ring.set_node(1, "Data 2")
token_ring.set_node(2, "Data 3")
token_ring.set_node(3, "Data 4")

# Run algorithm
token_ring.run()

'''
Termial : Python filename.py

Title : Mutual Exclusion using Token Ring Algorithm
Aim :To implement Token Ring based Mutual Exclusion Algorithm in Distributed Systems.

Mutual Exclusion means: Only one process can access the critical section at a time.

Critical Section (CS) is: Part of program where shared resource is accessed.

Examples: Shared file , Printer ,Database ,Shared variable

Without mutual exclusion: Multiple processes may access same resource simultaneously.This creates: Race Condition

Token Ring Algorithm is used to achieve mutual exclusion in distributed systems.
It uses: A special message called TOKEN
Only process having token can enter critical section.

Working of Token Ring Algorithm :
Step 1 : Processes are arranged in Logical Ring
    Example: P1 → P2 → P3 → P4 → P1
Step 2 : Initially one process gets TOKEN.
    Example:P1 has token
Step 3 : If process wants to enter Critical Section:
        It checks token availability.
Step 4 : If process has token: It enters Critical Section.
Step 5 : After completing work, Process passes token to next process.
